# Sensitive Tools

## Mark secrets-handling tools with sensitive: true
Any tool that processes secrets, credentials, or private keys must have `sensitive: true`
in its registry entry:
```ts
{ id: "jwt", ..., sensitive: true }
```
The bridge automatically applies `skipHistory: true` for sensitive tools — still pass
`{ skipHistory: true }` explicitly on every `callTool()` call (belt-and-suspenders).

## No draft persistence on sensitive tools
**Do NOT use `useDraftInput` or `useRestoreStringDraft` in sensitive tool components.**
These hooks persist input to localStorage — a privacy violation for secrets.

```ts
// ❌ Wrong for sensitive tools
const { setDraft } = useDraftInput(TOOL_ID);
useRestoreStringDraft(TOOL_ID, setInput);

// ✅ Correct — no draft hooks, every call gets skipHistory: true
await callTool(RUST_COMMAND, payload, { skipHistory: true });
```

Sensitive tools: JWT, AES, TOTP, Password, Basic Auth, API Key Generator,
and any future tool handling passwords, tokens, private keys, or PII.

